<div class="h-screen">
  <div class="overflow-auto h-full border p-4 text-base">
    <p class="mb-8">
      THIS VOLUNTEER AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), made on the date indicated with your signature is an
      understanding made between Technovation, a US 501c3 nonprofit, and <%= current_ambassador.full_name %>
      (henceforth referred to as Club Ambassador), an unpaid Technovation Girls Volunteer who organizes a
      Technovation Girls Club.  This agreement is valid for one year from the date indicated with your signature.
      The Club Ambassador may choose to end the Agreement with Technovation at any point before the end of the one-year
      time period. The Parties hereby agree to the following:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-decimal space-y-8 ml-4">
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Responsibilities of a Club Ambassador </span>
        <br>
        <span class="tw-hint">The Club Ambassador agrees to the following:</span>

        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Serve as the Club's primary contact</span>
            with external stakeholders, the Technovation headquarters team, and other volunteers & Mentors.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              Engage students that identify as female, or gender nonconforming from local schools and/or community-based organizations:
            </span>
            Recruit as needed to engage Technovation Girls participants, particularly those from underserved or
            underrepresented communities. (Club Ambassadors are expected to have 15 or more girls
            on teams registered on the technovationchallenge.org virtual platform. Volunteers that run Technovation
            on a smaller scale will be invited to be a Mentor.)
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Have procedures in place for participant safety:</span>
            This should include information on how girls can report potential issues when meeting with mentors or
            other adults. By signing this Agreement, the Club Ambassador agrees to complete applicable training and
            review resources as they become available. Training and resources can be found on the
            <%= link_to "Technovation safety page",
              ENV.fetch("INTERNET_SAFETY_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Ongoing season support via the Technovation Girls platform:</span>
            Assist girls to join teams and connect with local Mentors. Regularly check the Technovation Girls
            platform to ensure girls have registered and formed teams.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">As needed, cover any local operating costs of running Technovation:</span>
            While all of Technovation's resources & services are completely free, we recognize there may be other
            expenses associated with running the program, such as staff time, internet access, space usage, etc.
            Club Ambassadors are eligible to apply for funding from Technovation, we do not guarantee all
            program costs will be covered. [see Section 4 for more information].
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Coordinate with Technovation Girls funders (if applicable):</span>
            Club Ambassador will connect with and support foundation/corporate staff who fund Technovation Girls in the
            region to meet specific program deliverables (potential funding might be associated).
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Follow Club Ambassador Rules and Code of Conduct</span>
            Club Ambassador must adhere to the Rules,
            <%= link_to "Code of Conduct",
              ENV.fetch("CODE_OF_CONDUCT_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
            , and Safety instructions. Failure to adhere could result in the termination of Club Ambassador status.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Identify and support Mentors</span>
            Mentors can be teachers, organization staff, community members, professionals, university students or
            faculty. As needed, reach out to local companies and community Club Ambassadors to help support Technovation
            Girls participants. Club Ambassadors can organize Mentor orientation sessions and share Mentor training
            and support materials.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              Any additional staff or volunteers accessing student information on theTechnovation platform should
              have a Club Ambassador account
            </span>
            and sign this Volunteer Agreement as part of their Club Ambassador onboarding. These individuals must
            complete all Club Ambassador training and onboarding no later than November 30, 2025.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              Where available, work with Student Ambassadors (SAs)<sup>1</sup>
            </span>
            Please follow the guidelines below when working with SAs:
            <ul class="list-disc  ml-8">
              <li>
                If there are Technovation-approved SAs in your location, please connect with your local SAs virtually
                or in-person to understand their desired role and relationship with your Club. As desired by both
                parties, involve them in local Technovation recruitment and programming.
              </li>
              <li>
               It is important to note that:
               <ul>
                 <li>
                   Student Ambassadors are NOT responsible for recruiting adult mentors for teams and should
                   not meet one-on-one with Technovation volunteers.
                 </li>
                 <li>
                   Student Ambassadors are not expected to fundraise.
                 </li>
                 <li>
                   If Technovation provides the Student Ambassador's funding for program support and/or to purchase a
                   technological device, the Club may need to help receive and transfer funding to the SA and/or
                   their parent/guardian. Funding sent from Technovation to SAs is intended only for use by the named SA.
                 </li>
               </ul>
             </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">As needed, organize events</span>
            such as information sessions, Launch Workshops, Mentor training sessions, field trips, and/or Celebration
            Events. Technovation does not require any Club to hold any in-person events. Please adhere to any health
            restrictions, permit requirements, or other legal conditions required by your state/province and country.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Reporting:</span>
            Club Ambassador agrees to complete any required documentation during the season such as their profile on the
            Technovation platform, and any required Club reports. These reports help our team understand local needs and
            best practices to better support our global community.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Share alumnae stories and in-season highlights:</span>
            Club Ambassador will share success stories and alumnae achievements with Technovation to help raise the
            visibility of the program and its impact.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Cross-promote:</span>
            Club Ambassador agrees to promote Technovation Girls whenever possible and relevant through websites,
            social media, press, promotional materials, and public occasions. Club Ambassador must mention and recognize
            Technovation [refer to Section 3] in local press coverage and interviews related to the Technovation Girls
            teams/program<sup>2</sup>. If managing a Technovation social media page, the Club Ambassador will read and abide by the
            <%= link_to "Technovation's Social Media Guidelines",
              ENV.fetch("SOCIAL_MEDIA_GUIDELINES_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="tw-hint mt-8">
          <sup>1</sup> SAs are student leaders selected by Technovation who recruit and support students in their
          school or region to participate in the Technovation program
        </p>
        <p class="tw-hint">
          <sup>2</sup>  Technovation Girls social media handles: @technovationglobal [Facebook, Instagram]
          @technovation [Twitter, LinkedIn]
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Adherence to the Technovation Brand</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Refer to</span>
            <%= link_to "Technovation's Brand Guidelines",
              ENV.fetch("BRAND_GUIDELINES_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
            when developing customized, local materials. Technovation reserves the right to review and approve, or
            reject, any promotional materials, merchandise, marketing, websites, events, and/or written reference to
            Technovation and Technovation Girls before distribution or upon discovery.
          </li>
          <li>
            Any regional websites or webpages for Clubs must
            <span class="font-semibold">
              reference Technovation as the organization running the global Technovation Girls program and link back to
              Technovation.org.
            </span>
            Sample language and other branding collateral are in the
            <%= link_to "Regional Web Style Guide.",
              ENV.fetch("REGIONAL_WEB_STYLE_GUIDE_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            Club Ambassadors will portray their relationship to Technovation and Technovation Girls accurately and will
            not suggest they run the global Technovation Girls program or that they founded Technovation Girls. It must
            be clear that the Club Ambassadors is running a local Club of a global program
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              Get approval for press releases.
            </span>
            Club Ambassadors must send all press releases for approval to Technovation’s Marketing and Communication
            team at <%= mail_to "press@technovation.org" %> at least one week in advance. Technovation may request edits to ensure
            alignment with the Technovation Girls brand. Club Ambassadors must also secure approval for any quotes
            attributed to Technovation staff members or the organization as a whole.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              Technovation's regional and Club social media accounts should follow
              <%= link_to "Technovation's Social Media Guidelines",
                ENV.fetch("SOCIAL_MEDIA_GUIDELINES_URL"),
                target: "_blank",
                class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
              and
            </span>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-6">
              <li>Complete this
                <%= link_to "this form",
                  "https://forms.gle/sY9TUJjgAmkc1UES8",
                  target: "_blank",
                  class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
                to (1) report the Technovation social media page(s) your Club is managing and/or
                (2) indicate which channels you would like to start a social media page on. Please complete this form
                for every season.
              </li>
              <li>
                Admins of Technovation social media pages must be 18 or older.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Intellectual Property Rights</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            Technovation retains ownership of all curricula, training materials, social media content, and other
            information (i.e. the Materials) created for the Technovation Girls program and grants the Club Ambassadors
            a non-exclusive right to access and use these Materials for the purpose of supporting the Technovation Girls program.
          </li>
          <li>
            Technovation makes no representation, warranty, guarantee, or undertaking, that the Materials are entirely
            accurate or free from bugs, errors, or mistakes, or that the Materials will meet Club Ambassadors’s requirements.
            Club Ambassadors must ensure that the Materials are suitable for Club Ambassadors’s requirements.
          </li>
          <li>
            Technovation retains ownership of the Technovation name and logo. The Club Ambassadors may not use Technovation
            or the logo in the name or branding of the local Club unless given written permission by Technovation.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Rules</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Fundraising and Financial Support:</span>
            This Agreement does not secure any financial support from Technovation to the approved Club Ambassadors or
            vice versa. If Technovation and the Club Ambassador are involved in joint fundraising, the decision to share
            financial resources will be negotiated in the terms and conditions of the specific grant, and at the discretion
            of Technovation. Technovation may, at its discretion, offer financial support to specific Club Ambassadors
            based on criteria established by Technovation. When fundraising, the Club Ambassador must make it clear
            in the request for funds that the Club Ambassador is fundraising for the local Technovation Club and not as
            Technovation headquarters.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Discrimination is prohibited.</span>
            Participants of any socioeconomic background, academic record, ethnicity, race, religion, and sexual
            orientation are to be included in Technovation Girls' programming. While only
            <%= link_to "girls",
              "https://www.technovation.org/diversity-equity-inclusion-statement/",
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
            can participate in the
            competition, the curriculum is available to everyone.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Girls cannot be charged to participate.</span>
            If there is a specific instance where a Club Ambassador feels they need to charge participants a fee, they
            should first contact their Technovation point of contact to discuss the situation before collecting any funds.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">
              The Club Ambassador is responsible for securing and retaining media and photo consent
            </span>
            from every individual appearing in a photo they share with Technovation staff. It is assumed that the Club
            Ambassadors will only share photos of individuals who have consented to have their photo taken and potentially
            shared with the global Technovation community.
          </li>
          <li>
            Club Ambassadors are responsible for following local privacy laws.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Responsibilities of Technovation</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            Provide access to Technovation Girls’ free, updated <span class="font-semibold">curricula</span> and associated Materials.
          </li>
          <li>
            Provide <span class="font-semibold">participant information</span> for participants within the Club Ambassador’s geographic region
            via access to our platform and any survey results requested by the Club Ambassador.
          </li>
          <li>
            Provide a <span class="font-semibold">dedicated staff point of contact.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            Provide <span class="font-semibold">training and support</span> throughout the season for Club Ambassadors, including
            an Ambassador resource page.
          </li>
          <li>
            Provide access to <span class="font-semibold">marketing collateral</span> and
            <%= link_to "brand guidelines.",
              ENV.fetch("BRAND_GUIDELINES_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Organize the global competition and World Summit</span> to motivate and celebrate participants. Cover
            educational stipends and costs of participation and travel for finalist teams, if applicable.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Confidentiality Rules</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            Club Ambassador may have access to Confidential information <sup>3</sup> in connection with the program. Confidential
            information may not be disclosed to others not included in this agreement or the Club Ambassadors Agreement.
          </li>
          <li>
            Club Ambassador shall use Confidential information only in connection with and to benefit the Technovation
            Girls program and participants.
          </li>
          <li>
            Any party who will be sharing any participant work publicly shall only share materials of participants
            who have media consent on file with Technovation.
          </li>
          <li>
            All parties shall comply with local laws around data privacy such as GDPR regulations for European participants.
          </li>
          <li>
            Should there be a breach of information and/or confidentiality, Technovation reserves the right to
            remove any involved parties from their roles with Technovation.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="tw-hint mt-8">
          <sup>3</sup> Definition of Confidential includes any information about Technovation Girls participants or volunteers
          including but not limited to names, email addresses, locations (cities), and submission information.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Liability Waiver</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            The Club Ambassador understands that there are risks of harm associated with activities, events, locations,
            people, or organizations, related to their volunteer service.
          </li>
          <li>
            The Club Ambassador understands that they are responsible for their own safety during their volunteer
            service, and states that they have the skills and abilities needed to serve as a Volunteer safely.
            The Volunteer agrees not to hold Technovation liable for any harms or losses they may suffer while serving
            as a volunteer or while participating in any activities or events connected with the Technovation Girls program.
          </li>
          <li>
            Any Volunteer working for an organization partnering with Technovation understands that they need to follow
            their organization’s rules in regard to liability.
          </li>
          <li>
            The Club Ambassador agrees not to sue or make any claim, including any claim of negligence, against
            Technovation for any expenses, damages, losses, or harms that may occur from any activity, event, location,
            person, or organization relating to their service as a Technovation Girls volunteer.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Safety</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            Technovation created resources for all its volunteers, including Club Ambassadors,
            mentors, and judges, to ensure the safety of its participants.
            <span class="font-semibold">
              By signing this Agreement,the Club Ambassador agrees to complete applicable training and review
              resources as they become available.
            </span>
            Training and resources can be found on the
            <%= link_to "Technovation safety page.",
              ENV.fetch("INTERNET_SAFETY_URL"),
              target: "_blank",
              class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Use of Likeness Release</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            Club Ambassador agrees that Technovation may produce or participate in the production and/or dissemination
            of video (including team submissions), motion picture, audio recording, web page, public relations, or
            still photograph productions, broadcasting, and/or publication of printed and digital assets which may
            involve the use of Club Ambassador’s name, photo, likenesses, or voices. Club Ambassador agrees that such
            productions may be used for educational, exhibition, promotional, advertising, or other purposes by
            Technovation and/or its Club Ambassadors. Technovation will always obtain consent for using footage that
            includes minors.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Termination and Resignation</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Termination of a Club Ambassador:</span> A Club Ambassador serves at the
            discretion of Technovation, and Technovation may terminate the volunteer relationship at any time for
            any reason. Main reasons for termination:
            <ul class="ml-6 list-disc">
              <li>
                Club Ambassador violates any section of this Agreement or the Code of Conduct.
              </li>
              <li>
                Club Ambassador becomes inactive - Inactivity is defined by two or more of the following:
                having less than 10 girls registered for the program in their region, little to no interactions
                with Technovation staff, no communication with other Club Ambassadors, and not attending webinars or training.
                <br>
                <span class="tw-hint">
                  If terminated, Club Ambassador must immediately refrain from any further action related to
                  Technovation Girls or communication with program participants as a Club Ambassador.
                </span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Resignation:</span>
            If a Club Ambassador wishes to resign, he/she should try to find a replacement and help transition the program
            to the new Club Ambassador whenever possible
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Agreement Termination</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Termination Rights:</span>
            Suspension or Termination Due to Club Ambassadors Breach or Change of Content.  Technovation may suspend
            or terminate Club Ambassadors’s right to use the Copyrights, Marks, and/or Materials immediately upon
            notice to Club Ambassadors at any time upon such notice if (a) Club Ambassadors violates any term of this
            Agreement or (b) Club Ambassadors undergoes any material change in ownership or organizational control.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Technovation Complaint Process</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            If a Club Ambassador would like to raise concerns over the program delivery in their country,
            communication or conduct with Technovation staff, judging results, a termination decision, or
            any other subject, he/she should contact Technovation’s Senior Program Director, Rebecca Anderson
            rebecca@technovation.org. Club Ambassadors shall not send communication to teams and/or mentors
            regarding disputes.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>

      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold">Choice of Law</span>
        <ol class="ml-6 list-decimal space-y-4">
          <li>
            This Agreement is governed by the laws of California.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
